I came up with this awhile ago when I was playing with cooperative LLM agents. It is the simplest implementation of a message bus that I could think of. The architecture is very simple. Let&#39;s start with the following barebones python.
def main(): print(&quot;Hello, world.&quot;) if __name__==&quot;__main__&quot;: main() Let&#39;s begin by looking at how we interact with our bus. In the main() function, add the following:
bus = MessageBus() def callback(message: str): print(f&quot;Received message &#39;{message}&#39;&quot;) Now we need to sort out the bus.
